<subSubSection id="83C0A3EC7DE147694A411EE157DD4771" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="CADE21C8552C4123DE93AA192726D061" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2873AE69E85AC93EB406E4CE26EDAD2C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
On roadsides around 1200 m in 
<normalizedToken id="0743B709AB1CB4509B52ECE066A49907" originalValue="Michoacán">Michoacan</normalizedToken>
in the same general area as 
<taxonomicName id="F6E3B187C84D556CC96762E78D0AD125" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fissifolia">
<emphasis id="127FEDC24C151AEE52C9E84F3D7CAD1F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea fissifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9D88CA37EC4ACB40B01F8086EC775235" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis id="C3DCB4F69330AEA0F02E58C47E071614" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
MEXICO. 
<normalizedToken id="4C98A86A3FE3DBCC91828809B975EFA5" originalValue="Michoacán">Michoacan</normalizedToken>
</emphasis>
: Aguililla, 
<emphasis id="CB0EA8AD9B3E480AE8FA056CBF3574E4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
J. 
<normalizedToken id="54036D510E2686787196D8CC104FA0CA" originalValue="González">Gonzalez</normalizedToken>
et al.
</emphasis>
412 (IEB); ibid., 
<emphasis id="1183A343C1082C49252E074FD2301D8D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. Carranza &amp; I. Silva</emphasis>
6665 (IEB)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="21417D79EF33E002AC71FBBE9C38472D" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="A06E4190AC041B7D0654CA7E346193D7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9B20645D854B0B52C420C93B817518F1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The corolla is suburceolate resembling that of 
<taxonomicName id="45725C7A4C386CB247F52D7AB0CF328D" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lobata">
<emphasis id="AD6D8E60F487197A5D187A2BE69A1DC4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea lobata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but is maroon in colour and the inflorescence is secund, not cymose as stated in the protologue. It is distinguished by the corolla colour, much longer secondary peduncles to 25 mm (not 12 mm) and longer sepal awns.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
